|i sonni e i polsi~: ^le vene e i polsi~ is also read,
but |i sonni~ has far greater MS. authority (Moore, ^Text.
Crit.~, p. 3-4); and besides, ^le vene~, &c., would mean `it
drained my life-blood,' and it is not his death which is here
referred to.  The plur. |sonni~ is found in Italian, though it
is rare.  Purg. xxxii. 78, where it occurs, is not a case in
point, for it used there of the sleep of several persons.
