..TEXT:
|per disdegnoso gusto~: `prompted by disdainful
feeling,' lit. `owing to my experience (taste) of the feeling of
disdain.'  It is often interpreted as meaning `owing to having
tasted of the disdain of others'; but to take |disdegnoso~
(`disdainful') in this sense seems to be doing violence to the
meaning of the adjective.  The disdain of others is expressed by
|disdegno~ in the following line.  |Ingiusto~, &c.: `when I was
just in my dealings with others, my feelings caused me to treat
myself unjustly.'
