..TEXT:
|il primo padrone~: Mars, to whom, according to the
story then current, a temple was erected in the time of Augustus;
but this was converted into a church of St. John the Baptist,
i.e. the old Cathedral of Florence, which is now the Baptistery
(Villani, i. 42, 60).
